
a) Display a list of all property names and their property idâ€™s for Owner Id: 1426

SELECT Property.Name, OwnerProperty.PropertyId, OwnerProperty.OwnerId
FROM Property
INNER JOIN OwnerProperty ON Property.Id = OwnerProperty.PropertyId
WHERE  (OwnerProperty.OwnerId = 1426)


b) Display the current home value for each property in question a)

SELECT Property.Name, PropertyHomeValue.Value
FROM OwnerProperty 
INNER JOIN Property ON OwnerProperty.PropertyId = Property.Id 
INNER JOIN PropertyHomeValue ON Property.Id = PropertyHomeValue.PropertyId
WHERE  (OwnerProperty.OwnerId = 1426)

c) For each property in question a), return the following:                                                                      
Using rental payment amount, rental payment frequency, tenant start date and tenant end date to write a query that returns the sum of all payments from start date to end date. 


Display the yield. 


d) Display all the jobs available

SELECT Job.PropertyId, Job.JobDescription, JobStatus.Status, JobMedia.IsActive, JobMedia.JobId
FROM Job
INNER JOIN JobMedia ON Job.Id = JobMedia.JobId
INNER JOIN JobStatus ON Job.JobStatusId = JobStatus.Id
WHERE  (JobStatus.Status = N'Open') AND (JobMedia.IsActive = 1)


e) Display all property names, current tenants first and last names and rental payments per week/ fortnight/month for the properties in question a)

SELECT Property.Name as PropertyName, CONCAT(Person.FirstName,' ' ,Person.LastName) as TenantName, TenantProperty.PaymentAmount,  TenantPaymentFrequencies.Name as PaymentFrequency
FROM   OwnerProperty 
INNER JOIN TenantProperty ON  OwnerProperty.PropertyId = TenantProperty.propertyid
INNER JOIN Property ON Property.Id = OwnerProperty.PropertyId 
INNER JOIN TenantPaymentFrequencies ON TenantPaymentFrequencies.Id = TenantProperty.paymentfrequencyid
INNER JOIN Person ON Person.Id = TenantProperty.TenantId
WHERE  (OwnerProperty.OwnerId = 1426)


